						<summary>

						<p>Slab near the image of Perumāl in the threshing ground, front side.</p>						

						<p>Vijayanagara: Sadāśivadēvarāya.</p>						

						<p>It is dated <hi rend="bold">Śaka 1476, Rākshasa, Kārttīka śu. 11,</hi> corresponding to 1555 A.D., October 26 Saturday.</p>						

						<p>Damaged. It seems to be a gift to god Chennakēśava of Malinēnipaṭnam situated in Siddhavaṭam-sīma. Name of the donor and donee are lost.</p>						

						</summary>
